gomodel:SYNGO_5026  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figures 2-4: 3D structures of spines of 8-week-old WT, Reelin-OE (overexpressing) and Dab1-cKO GFP/DAB-labeled granule cells were reconstructed with FIB/SEM microscopy. Reelin and Dab1 both altered newborn granule cells dendritic spine morphology.\n\nAuthors conclude from these analyses that \"This proves that spines are more irregularly shaped in 8-9 weeks Reelin-OE and Dab1-cKO neurons, and suggests that spine structural maturation is affected by the Reelin signaling. Synapse sphericity was smaller in Reelin-OE mice at 8-9 weeks, indicating greater complexity (Fig.4d).\". Experimental description: M&M: \"Conditional knockout Dab1 mice (Dab1-cKO) (Pramatarova et al. 2008) and Reelin-overexpressing (Reelin-OE, gamma strain) (Pujadas et al. 2010) mice were maintained on a C57BL/6 J background. \"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-18" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_5026" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

